Rating: 3
Wow - there I was, 6:45 and I had no idea what to serve for dinner...noticed a box of cilantro lime rice in the pantry, can of tomato sauce, had a couple of chicken breasts in the freezer, thought "I wonder if I could make some sort of quick Mexican dish out of these" and to Epicurious I went. Popped the chicken breasts in the microwave to defrost for 20 minutes and started cooking the rice while I figured out what I was going to make and found this recipe. Let's talk substitutions: Like I said above, had tomato sauce, not stewed tomatoes. I had no orange juice but I did have apple juice so I said "what the heck" and threw it in there. Luckily I always have chicken broth in the pantry and organic bottled lime juice (and lemon juice for that matter) in the fridge. I had just run out of garlic, but did have garlic powder (kept on adding by 1/2 tsps until it tasted right at 1.5 tsps). I seriously couldn't believe how tasty this dish turned out to be. Bottom line - within 40 minutes, including defrosting the chicken and cooking the rice, I had dinner on the table and everyone ate every last bite. This will now become a staple, and I'm sure it will taste even better with the right ingredients!

